================================================================================
                          PREAMBLE AND STATEMENT OF INTENT
================================================================================

This License governs the use, reproduction, modification, distribution, and
public performance of the software known as "Spectral Packet Engine" (the
"Software"), a bounded-domain spectral computation library for packet
simulation, modal decomposition, inverse reconstruction, and scientific data
workflows.

This License is designed to achieve the following objectives simultaneously:

  (a) Ensure that the Software remains perpetually available as open-source
      software that anyone may use, study, modify, and redistribute;

  (b) Ensure that any person or entity that modifies, extends, or builds upon
      the Software is legally required to make those modifications available to
      the public under the same terms, thereby guaranteeing that improvements
      flow back to the community;

  (c) Ensure that the Software and its author receive proper attribution in all
      derivative works, academic publications, commercial products, and public
      communications;

  (d) Provide an explicit, irrevocable grant of patent rights from each
      contributor, with automatic termination upon patent aggression;

  (e) Prevent any party from creating a substantially similar work and claiming
      it as independent or unrelated to this Software;

  (f) Encourage, through strong normative language, that users of this Software
      who derive commercial or academic value from it contribute financially to
      its continued development.

This License is intended to be enforceable under the laws of the Republic of
Turkey (FSEK Law No. 5846 on Intellectual and Artistic Works), the United States
(Title 17 U.S.C.; 35 U.S.C.), the European Union (Directive 2009/24/EC on the
legal protection of computer programs; Directive 2001/29/EC on copyright in the
information society), and any other jurisdiction that recognizes the Berne
Convention for the Protection of Literary and Artistic Works.

This License is a COPYRIGHT LICENSE.  It operates as a conditional grant of
rights under copyright law.  Violation of any condition of this License
constitutes copyright infringement, not merely breach of contract, and is
actionable under both statutory copyright law and contract law in all applicable
jurisdictions.

