         system libraries, general-purpose tools, or freely available source
         code that is used unmodified in building the Derivative Work but is
         not part of the Derivative Work itself.

     (c) The Source Code must be made available through at least one of the
         following mechanisms, at Your choice:

         (i)   Hosting the Source Code in a publicly accessible version control
               repository (e.g., GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket, or any other
               publicly accessible hosting platform) and providing a clear,
               conspicuous, and permanent link to such repository in all
