6.2  DONATION EXPECTATION.

     (a) If You or Your organization derive commercial value from the Software,
         including but not limited to: using the Software in a revenue-
         generating product or service; using the Software to reduce
         development costs; using the Software in paid research or consulting;
         or using the Software to train employees or students in connection
         with a commercial enterprise, You SHOULD make a financial contribution
         to the Software's development through the donation mechanism designated
         by the Licensor (currently specified in the official repository's
         FUNDING.yml or equivalent file).

     (b) The recommended contribution amounts are:

         (i)   Individual developers and students: voluntary, any amount;
         (ii)  Small organizations (fewer than 50 employees): at least $100 USD
               per year or equivalent in local currency;
         (iii) Medium organizations (50-500 employees): at least $500 USD per
               year or equivalent in local currency;
         (iv)  Large organizations (more than 500 employees): at least $2,000
               USD per year or equivalent in local currency.

     (c) The amounts in Section 6.2(b) are RECOMMENDED GUIDELINES, not legally
         binding obligations.  Failure to make a financial contribution does
         not constitute a violation of this License and does not result in
         termination of any rights granted herein.

     (d) Notwithstanding Section 6.2(c), any organization that derives
         significant commercial value from the Software and declines to make
         any voluntary contribution SHOULD consider whether its use of the
         Software without reciprocal support is consistent with the ethical
         principles of the open-source community and the sustainable
         development of shared scientific infrastructure.

